### Can we scrape or embed AROW?

|Method                                |Feasibility                                                                     |
|--------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Scrape data from AROW page            |❌ Not possible — it’s a compiled Unity WebGL binary; zero inspectable data feeds|
|Iframe embed of AROW Unity app        |⚠️ Possible technically; NASA’s CSP headers likely block cross-origin embedding  |
|Direct link to `nasa.gov/trackartemis`|✅ Always works; recommended as an authoritative reference                       |
|Download ephemeris files from the page|✅ Files are publicly linked at bottom of the NASA tracking page; version-stamped|
|State vectors when published by AROW  |✅ NASA commits to publishing these; watch the tracking page and @NASA_Orion     |

**Conclusion:** We cannot pull live telemetry from AROW directly. Our best approach is: (1) use NASA’s downloadable ephemeris for trajectory/position, (2) link prominently to AROW as the official NASA tool, and (3) monitor for any published state vector feeds as the mission progresses.

