## Section 7 — Moon Distance Warning

The simplified sinusoidal Moon model used in `artemislivetracker.com` produces **severe errors**. When tested against the ephemeris, the model predicted a closest Moon approach of ~150,540 km — versus the mission’s actual closest approach of ~9,650 km. That is a 140,000+ km error. **JPL Horizons is required for accurate Moon distance.** The API is free, CORS-accessible, and returns ECI state vectors for any solar system body.

```
JPL Horizons API example:
https://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/api/horizons.api?format=json
  &COMMAND=301          (Moon)
  &EPHEM_TYPE=VECTORS
  &CENTER=500@399       (Earth center)
  &START_TIME=2026-04-01
  &STOP_TIME=2026-04-11
  &STEP_SIZE=4h
  &VEC_TABLE=2
  &REF_FRAME=ICRF
```

